      "dialog_name": "☝️🤓 τhe nerds 🧠🥼",
      "dialog_type": "group",
      "sender": "vaN ττ",
      "text": "This is big.\n\n**Grayscale Bittensor Trust ETF (GTAO)** — filed with the SEC on **April 2, 2026** (yesterday).\n\nKey facts from the filing:\n\n• **S-1/A (Amendment No. 1)** — this is an amended registration statement, meaning they filed the original S-1 earlier and this is an update\n• **Issuer:** Grayscale Bittensor Trust (TAO), a Delaware statutory trust\n• **Ticker:** GTAO\n• **Currently:** Quoted on OTCQX (over-the-counter)\n• **Target:** Listing on **NYSE Arca** — this is the upgrade from OTC to a proper exchange-listed ETF\n• **Structure:** Holds actual TAO tokens, issues shares in baskets of 10,000\n• **Custodians:** Coinbase Custody + BitGo Trust Company\n• **Prime Broker:** Coinbase Inc.\n• **Administrator:** Bank of New York Mellon\n• **Legal:** Davis Polk & Wardwell (top-tier securities firm)\n• **Staking:** Currently NOT staking the TAO held in trust. Explicitly states no staking is happening and may never be permitted.\n• **Index:** CoinDesk Bittensor Benchmark Rate for NAV pricing\n\n**What this means:**\nGrayscale is converting their existing OTC Bittensor trust into a full NYSE-listed ETF. This is the same path they took with Bitcoin (GBTC) and Ethereum (ETHE). Once effective, institutional investors, retirement accounts, and traditional brokerages can buy TAO exposure through a regulated ETF.\n\nThis is the institutional on-ramp for Bittensor. 🦞",
      "date": "2026-04-03T04:08:11+00:00",
      "reply_to_id": null
    },
